00:37:21,660 --> 00:37:24,010
Indeed! Therefore you—

288
00:37:27,400 --> 00:37:31,470
That reminds me. I have yet to get your name.

289
00:37:35,030 --> 00:37:36,450
Not that I need to.

290
00:37:36,450 --> 00:37:41,110
The name you bore once before is meaningless hereafter.

291
00:37:42,290 --> 00:37:43,860
Welcome to the world of the night,

292
00:37:45,860 --> 00:37:48,780
my servant.

293
00:38:12,860 --> 00:38:13,470
Where...

294
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:17,730
Where are we?

295
00:38:22,980 --> 00:38:26,890
I believe it was called a cram school.

296
00:38:26,890 --> 00:38:31,620
It went bankrupt a few years ago and is abandoned now.

297
00:38:31,620 --> 00:38:34,840
A suitable place to withdraw to.

298
00:38:37,120 --> 00:38:39,710
Next question, Kiss-shot.

299
00:38:39,710 --> 00:38:40,750
Hold on!

300
00:38:40,750 --> 00:38:44,460
I told you to call me Heart-under-blade!

301
00:38:44,990 --> 00:38:46,740
That's way too long.

302
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:49,450
I prefer Kiss-shot. It's short.

303
00:38:50,120 --> 00:38:52,970
Can't I call you that?

304
00:38:54,960 --> 00:38:55,890
Oh well.

305
00:38:56,650 --> 00:39:01,190
If you prefer it, so shall it be.

306
00:39:01,960 --> 00:39:03,540
I have no reason to forbid it.

307
00:39:05,510 --> 00:39:06,440
So?

308
00:39:06,850 --> 00:39:08,950
What is your next question?

309
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:15,600
I turned into a vampire, right?

310
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:17,340
Is it not obvious?

311
00:39:17,340 --> 00:39:20,290
Do I need to spell it out for you?

312
00:39:20,290 --> 00:39:24,660
You became my kin, my servant.

313
00:39:24,660 --> 00:39:26,030
Consider it an honor.

314
00:39:26,780 --> 00:39:28,140
Your servant...

315
00:39:29,470 --> 00:39:34,670
Why do you have a child's body now?

316
00:39:34,670 --> 00:39:39,180
Earlier you were more, uh, mature—

317
00:39:40,450 --> 00:39:42,690
Sorry for not being more "mature"!

318
00:39:42,690 --> 00:39:45,070
That's not what I meant.

319
00:39:45,070 --> 00:39:46,570
Mature

320
00:39:47,070 --> 00:39:48,570
And

321
00:39:51,240 --> 00:39:53,450
Your limbs were severed

322
00:39:55,200 --> 00:39:58,450
I took all your blood,

323
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:01,730
but it was insufficient.

324
00:40:01,730 --> 00:40:05,260
Therefore I took a form I could sustain.

325
00:40:05,260 --> 00:40:07,460
Still better than perishing.

326
00:40:07,900 --> 00:40:11,390
Then again, I can only sustain a
minimum amount of immortality,

327
00:40:11,390 --> 00:40:15,500
and most of my vampire powers are unavailable now.

328
00:40:15,500 --> 00:40:17,350
Inconvenient indeed.

329
00:40:17,350 --> 00:40:17,470
Flashback

330
00:40:18,100 --> 00:40:18,220
Flashback

331
00:40:18,850 --> 00:40:18,970
Flashback

332
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:25,630
My limbs are restored, as you can see.

333
00:40:26,350 --> 00:40:29,150
I could at least regenerate the form,
if not the power to fill it.

334
00:40:29,650 --> 00:40:32,910
This should suffice for now.

335
00:40:32,910 --> 00:40:39,340
That said, do not forget that you are my servant.

336
00:40:39,340 --> 00:40:45,080
I may look this way now,
but I am a vampire who has lived for five centuries.

337
00:40:45,410 --> 00:40:48,540
You are but a newborn as a vampire.

338
00:40:48,540 --> 00:40:52,420
Know your place when you address me.

339
00:40:52,830 --> 00:40:54,390
Oh.

340
00:40:54,390 --> 00:40:57,670
Make your replies clear.

341
00:40:57,670 --> 00:40:59,680
Do you really understand?

342
00:40:59,980 --> 00:41:02,690
I do...

343
00:41:02,690 --> 00:41:07,310
Then as a sign of your obedience, pat my head.

344
00:41:20,080 --> 00:41:21,500
That should do.

345
00:41:32,450 --> 00:41:36,160
Why did you turn me into a vampire?

346
00:41:37,580 --> 00:41:42,560
I was prepared to die being sucked dry by you.

347
00:41:43,410 --> 00:41:46,690
I did not intend to.

348
00:41:46,690 --> 00:41:51,970
All who have their blood drunk by a vampire will,
without exception, turn into vampires.

349
00:41:51,970 --> 00:41:53,630
That is all.

350
00:41:53,630 --> 00:41:56,000
I see...

351
00:41:56,570 --> 00:42:00,850
It is quite convenient for me.

352
00:42:01,620 --> 00:42:05,540
There is something I need you to do.

353
00:42:06,180 --> 00:42:10,970
Your blood alone only allows me to regenerate so much.

354
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:14,700
I am far from my full potential.

355
00:42:14,700 --> 00:42:18,860
Which is why you shall act in my stead.

356
00:42:20,140 --> 00:42:21,810
What do you want from me?

357
00:42:29,690 --> 00:42:30,810
Can I...

358
00:42:33,420 --> 00:42:37,820
Can I return to being human?

359
00:42:41,430 --> 00:42:43,910
I thought so.

360
00:42:43,910 --> 00:42:46,370
I was prepared for that question.

361
00:42:46,370 --> 00:42:48,710
So? Can I?!

362
00:42:48,710 --> 00:42:49,580
You can.

363
00:42:51,450 --> 00:42:52,820
I can guarantee that.

364
00:42:53,530 --> 00:42:55,460
I give you my word if needed.

365
00:43:10,980 --> 00:43:14,730
The names of three people who robbed Kiss-shot of parts of her body.

366
00:43:21,970 --> 00:43:26,720
Those three are specialist vampire slayers.

367
00:43:26,720 --> 00:43:29,730
They're the ones that killed you?

368
00:43:29,730 --> 00:43:31,630
Are you out of your mind?

369
00:43:31,630 --> 00:43:33,250
They have yet to finish me off.

370
00:43:33,850 --> 00:43:36,970
However, they took my limbs.

371
00:43:36,970 --> 00:43:39,590
I have very little regenerative power left too.

372
00:43:40,270 --> 00:43:44,390
I have no chance of standing against them now.

373
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:52,530
You shall face those three and take back my limbs.

374
00:43:52,530 --> 00:43:53,400
Huh?

375
00:43:58,220 --> 00:44:02,820
"You shall" as if it was that simple.

376
00:44:02,820 --> 00:44:08,590
To make you human once again, I must regain my full power.

377
00:44:08,590 --> 00:44:11,120
I must be whole again.

378
00:44:11,770 --> 00:44:16,670
My limbs are absolutely necessary for that.

379
00:44:17,390 --> 00:44:22,580
But I can't fight at all.

380
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:26,800
Won't I just get slain instead?

381
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:28,110
Fool.

382
00:44:28,110 --> 00:44:31,690
You still think as if you were human.

383
00:44:32,220 --> 00:44:34,690
You are now my kin.

384
00:44:35,240 --> 00:44:39,010
Now that I am weakened to a bare minimum,

385
00:44:39,010 --> 00:44:43,700
while I am still a top-class vampire, you could still kill me.

386
00:44:44,430 --> 00:44:48,830
So you're a weak vampire?

387
00:44:48,830 --> 00:44:50,260
No!

388
00:45:04,410 --> 00:45:09,880
You're weakened, so I might be stronger than you at this point,

389
00:45:09,880 --> 00:45:16,000
but those three managed to take your limbs when you were whole and at full power.

390
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:16,900
How could I—

391
00:45:17,340 --> 00:45:20,830
I was at a disadvantage because they came at me at once.

392
00:45:20,830 --> 00:45:22,510
I took them lightly.

393
00:45:24,460 --> 00:45:29,180
What I mean is that as long as you take on them one by one,

394
00:45:29,180 --> 00:45:31,660
they shall stand no chance against you.

395
00:45:32,030 --> 00:45:35,170
Simply put: it is an easy task.

396
00:47:03,220 --> 00:47:05,420
What now?

397
00:48:05,110 --> 00:48:05,360
Dismember

398
00:48:09,570 --> 00:48:12,490
Would you at least hear me out?!

399
00:48:12,490 --> 00:48:12,740
Dismember

400
00:48:13,050 --> 00:48:14,740
I'm human!

401
00:48:15,600 --> 00:48:20,000
Do you want to murder a fellow human?!

402
00:48:17,910 --> 00:48:18,040
Mur

403
00:48:18,040 --> 00:48:18,160
der

