You seem so worked up.

415
00:50:08,790 --> 00:50:10,940
Did something nice happen to you?

416
00:50:16,290 --> 00:50:19,280
Let's just go home for now, Araragi.

417
00:50:20,130 --> 00:50:21,410
Home?

418
00:50:23,970 --> 00:50:26,630
To that old abandoned cram school.

419
00:50:27,580 --> 00:50:28,170
Huh?

420
00:50:30,700 --> 00:50:31,670
Hold on a second!

421
00:50:31,670 --> 00:50:34,250
How do you know about that?

422
00:50:35,310 --> 00:50:37,050
Why are you surprised?

423
00:50:37,050 --> 00:50:41,930
I'm the one who told her about it.

424
00:50:43,740 --> 00:50:47,460
Failing to do the right thing is the sign of cowardice.

425
00:50:48,220 --> 00:50:54,870
Heart-under-blade looked like she was in trouble,
dragging your body around,

426
00:50:54,870 --> 00:50:57,200
so I gave her a good spot.

427
00:50:59,130 --> 00:51:02,480
Who are you?

428
00:51:03,180 --> 00:51:06,200
I'm just an old fart who happened to pass by.

429
00:51:09,980 --> 00:51:11,980
Don't worry.

430
00:51:11,980 --> 00:51:15,630
I'm no vampire slayer or specialist.

431
00:51:16,330 --> 00:51:20,890
I practice in a much wider field.

432
00:51:21,200 --> 00:51:24,680
I'll introduce myself properly later.

433
00:51:28,260 --> 00:51:29,470
You're back!

434
00:51:31,940 --> 00:51:33,770
Who is that behind you?

435
00:51:33,770 --> 00:51:35,150
I feel like I've met you before.

436
00:51:35,150 --> 00:51:36,590
That's so mean.

437
00:51:36,590 --> 00:51:38,400
Is that all you remember of me?

438
00:51:39,570 --> 00:51:40,820
So?

439
00:51:41,310 --> 00:51:42,570
How did it go?

440
00:51:51,580 --> 00:51:53,750
This is a problem.

441
00:51:53,750 --> 00:51:57,450
Those three are still working together.

442
00:51:57,450 --> 00:52:04,010
They took you out even at your full power.

443
00:52:04,010 --> 00:52:08,220
I stand no chance against them.

444
00:52:08,220 --> 00:52:11,300
Which is why I told you to take them on one by one!

445
00:52:11,300 --> 00:52:14,110
They're together. It's not happening.

446
00:52:14,650 --> 00:52:20,710
You said we could just lay low,
but who knows when they find us he—

447
00:52:20,710 --> 00:52:22,860
Don't worry about that.

448
00:52:23,160 --> 00:52:29,310
I drew up a boundary around here while you were asleep.

449
00:52:30,070 --> 00:52:31,520
A boundary?

450
00:52:31,520 --> 00:52:33,710
Like a barrier?

451
00:52:33,710 --> 00:52:35,630
Something like that.

452
00:52:37,000 --> 00:52:40,590
What's up with you, exactly?

453
00:52:40,950 --> 00:52:44,910
Why did you help Kiss-shot and me?

454
00:52:45,880 --> 00:52:48,540
I realize you're not an enemy,

455
00:52:48,540 --> 00:52:51,810
but I doubt you'd be on our side either.

456
00:52:57,090 --> 00:52:59,690
Jeez, you're so cruel.

457
00:53:00,080 --> 00:53:03,200
I'm maintaining the balance.

458
00:53:03,570 --> 00:53:06,730
Consider that my job.

459
00:53:06,730 --> 00:53:09,330
I bridge this side and the other.

460
00:53:10,620 --> 00:53:12,330
Introduce yourself.

461
00:53:12,930 --> 00:53:14,740
You said you would.

462
00:53:15,210 --> 00:53:17,170
Spin

463
00:53:15,210 --> 00:53:16,170
3

464
00:53:16,170 --> 00:53:17,170
2

465
00:53:19,260 --> 00:53:20,460
Oshino Meme.

466
00:53:20,460 --> 00:53:21,340
Oshino Meme

467
00:53:21,340 --> 00:53:23,960
I'm like a rolling stone.

468
00:53:23,960 --> 00:53:27,620
I'm kind of an authority on monsters and apparitions.

469
00:53:29,540 --> 00:53:34,990
Unlike those three, I'm not great at exorcising though.

470
00:53:34,990 --> 00:53:36,560
Not great?

471
00:53:37,420 --> 00:53:39,740
Let me rephrase that.

472
00:53:39,740 --> 00:53:41,820
I'm not a fan of it.

473
00:53:41,820 --> 00:53:44,860
Doesn't that make you a specialist then?

474
00:53:45,140 --> 00:53:48,120
Maintaining the balance is my specialty.

475
00:53:48,610 --> 00:53:51,620
I negotiate from neutral ground.

476
00:53:52,180 --> 00:53:54,870
Call me a mediator.

477
00:53:56,030 --> 00:53:57,160
Negotiation?

478
00:53:57,900 --> 00:54:01,170
Bridging this side and the other?

479
00:54:02,590 --> 00:54:06,220
Where is "this side" and what's "the other"?

480
00:54:06,720 --> 00:54:07,970
Speech / Voice

481
00:54:06,720 --> 00:54:09,970
Are the two sides humans and monsters?

482
00:54:10,220 --> 00:54:12,100
In that case, now I

483
00:54:12,100 --> 00:54:13,980
belong to which side?

484
00:54:14,340 --> 00:54:15,350
Monsters?

485
00:54:15,820 --> 00:54:17,000
That's good.

486
00:54:17,000 --> 00:54:18,980
I prefer to call them oddities though.

487
00:54:20,360 --> 00:54:21,110
Oddity

488
00:54:21,110 --> 00:54:24,990
And she's the oddity slayer.

489
00:54:25,320 --> 00:54:29,890
She's a rare kind of vampire who can drain energy from oddities.

490
00:54:29,890 --> 00:54:33,390
That makes her pretty famous actually.

491
00:54:36,910 --> 00:54:41,510
I listened to your little chat earlier.

492
00:54:42,340 --> 00:54:45,670
Quite the pinch you're in.

493
00:54:45,670 --> 00:54:49,040
I didn't expect things to take such a difficult turn.

494
00:54:49,040 --> 00:54:50,680
There is nothing difficult about it.

495
00:54:50,680 --> 00:54:52,260
It is extremely simple.

496
00:54:52,570 --> 00:54:57,270
In the eyes of an undying vampire, maybe.

497
00:54:58,520 --> 00:55:01,780
It's quite the trouble for us humans.

498
00:55:01,780 --> 00:55:03,530
Right, Araragi?

499
00:55:09,260 --> 00:55:13,450
Also, Heart-under-blade,

500
00:55:13,900 --> 00:55:20,580
I liked how you agreed to return
your kin Araragi to being human.

501
00:55:31,920 --> 00:55:35,350
Should I mediate for you?

502
00:55:36,850 --> 00:55:42,280
Between us and those three?

503
00:55:42,280 --> 00:55:43,480
Who else?

504
00:55:44,520 --> 00:55:47,990
So you'll help us?

505
00:55:48,660 --> 00:55:51,210
No. But I'll lend you a hand.

506
00:55:51,820 --> 00:55:57,810
The balance feels off as it is right now.

507
00:55:57,810 --> 00:55:59,870
It's like I'm watching bullies get their way.

508
00:56:01,410 --> 00:56:07,330
Of course, since it's my job, I'm not gonna do it for free.

509
00:56:07,980 --> 00:56:09,130
Hm...

510
00:56:10,780 --> 00:56:12,510
How about 2 million?

511
00:56:12,820 --> 00:56:14,260
2 million?!

512
00:56:13,510 --> 00:56:14,260
Akasegawa

513
00:56:14,860 --> 00:56:17,600
You pay when you can, and I won't bother you about it.

514
00:56:17,600 --> 00:56:22,770
That much is the least I must ask to maintain the balance.

515
00:56:23,690 --> 00:56:26,020
But...

516
00:56:28,960 --> 00:56:31,650
Shall we hear your exact plan?

517
00:56:34,770 --> 00:56:37,660
Negotiations sound nice, but it is not so easy.

518
00:56:38,110 --> 00:56:41,160
Trying to convince those three is futile.

519
00:56:41,160 --> 00:56:45,290
All I can do is ask

520
00:56:47,380 --> 00:56:49,130
earnestly.

521
00:56:49,580 --> 00:56:53,890
If asking doesn't work, more dangerous ideas get involved.

522
00:56:53,890 --> 00:56:57,640
If we can at least communicate, we can play a game.

523
00:56:58,070 --> 00:57:00,890
A game?

524
00:57:02,390 --> 00:57:06,550
Firstly, we need to separate them.

525
00:57:06,550 --> 00:57:14,070
You said dealing with them
one by one shouldn't be an issue.

526
00:57:14,070 --> 00:57:17,030
We should make that happen then.

527
00:57:17,030 --> 00:57:22,660
Boy, how do you plan to negotiate with them in the first place?

528
00:57:23,040 --> 00:57:26,020
The details are a trade secret.

529
00:57:26,020 --> 00:57:28,670
I'll level the playing field,

530
00:57:29,130 --> 00:57:33,510
and Araragi can get back your limbs.

531
00:57:34,800 --> 00:57:40,210
If you regain your limbs, you also regain your full power,

532
00:57:40,210 --> 00:57:45,520
which means you can return Araragi to human.

533
00:57:48,050 --> 00:57:49,270
Servant!

534
00:57:50,850 --> 00:57:53,890
I cannot procure human money.

535
00:57:53,890 --> 00:57:58,520
I have no idea how heavy a debt of 2 million is.

536
00:57:59,140 --> 00:58:02,290
Can you shoulder it?

537
00:58:05,820 --> 00:58:07,610
Do not worry.

538
00:58:07,610 --> 00:58:09,960
His skills are real.

539
00:58:10,490 --> 00:58:14,220
I may be weak now, but even I can see that.

540
00:58:16,380 --> 00:58:18,350
I don't have that much saved,

541
00:58:19,280 --> 00:58:21,830
but if I get to pay when I can
and you don't press me about it,

542
00:58:21,830 --> 00:58:25,980
and I don't need collateral or a guarantor,

543
00:58:27,080 --> 00:58:28,350
